# .legitignore — Legit Secret Scanning suppressions.
#
# Format: one entry per line, # for comments. Three entry shapes (per
# the Legit alert annotation documentation):
#
#   value_<hash>     ignores every occurrence of this secret value
#                    repo-wide and across history. Robust to history
#                    rewrites that change instance hashes.
#   instance_<hash>  ignores one specific (commit, file, line) match.
#   <glob>           file/dir glob; ignores all secrets under the path.

# "POSTGRES_PASSWORD_FILE" is the env-var NAME the operator injects on
# the metadata container to point dedicated-pensieve at its Postgres
# credentials Secret (the actual password lives in a mounted
# Kubernetes Secret at the path this env var points to). Legit's
# generic-password rule flags the literal because the word
# "PASSWORD" appears in it. Value-based suppression so the rule stays
# silent even after history rewrites.
value_74C1494275B3EC5601DEB210A6ACA034

# FB-896 auth test fixtures. These are fake credential values hard-coded in
# unit tests (never real secrets): the literal admin-password Secret key name
# "password" (instance_auth_test.go, fireboltinstance_webhook_test.go), and the
# fake admin-Secret names "admin-creds" and "a-different-secret" used to assert
# Secret-ref plumbing and drift detection. Legit's high-entropy/generic-password
# rules flag them by proximity to "Password"/"Admin" field names. Value-based
# suppression (inline `// legit:ignore-secrets` is not honored by this
# integration — the operator's only working suppression is this file).
value_536FF1BE56D281A30D1704BBA91C043C
value_A6AE22CADAC3B0BEE06B0684CFA2B2F8
value_ABC139F439D41936CB2EB99E927041D9
